  "text": "The only way to afford the PTO for a decent vacation is by digging deep into your own morally-grey pocket. Many of you would do anything for a little extra PTO. After a long, hard week in the workplace, a vacation starts to seem like the only antidote for a poisonous job and a collection of mean coworkers. Even with dreams of white sand, turquoise beaches, and an all-inclusive swim-up bar dancing in your head, there is still a limit to what we'd do for a trip. \"Would I do anything for a vacation?\" you wonder.But there's a line in the sand of common decency that mustn't be crossed, even for the sake of a well-deserved vacay. However, for some, the desperate and the morally grey, ethics hardly matter when it comes to PTO. This woman has only endured 6 months of 2025 but has already spent her annual PTO, and in a shocking turn of events, she spilled the beans on the immoral lengths that she was willing to go to get a few more days off—even if it meant disrespecting everyone in the office with a diabolical lie. The image does not depict the actual subjects of the story. Subjects are models. Stay up to date by following us on Facebook! Tags Scroll Down For The Next Article Trending Now Couple excitedly announces that they bought a home, distant cousin they haven't spoken to in years demands they let her stay in the guest room for free: ‘Some people only act like family when it’s convenient.’ 01 ‘Now I sell by myself and make tons more money’: Friends try to hijack a homemade ice cream business by eating the inventory, inviting freeloaders, and cutting out the owner, forcing the real entrepreneur to take everything and leave 02 20+ Workers who realized the customer was not always right: 'An unhappy customer? Oh no' 03 Manager blocks employee from getting a promotion, driving them to quit their job, years later same manager applies to a position in employee's new company: ‘I got her interview canceled’ 04 Employee quits job without notice after accepting a job